gomodel:SYNGO_1929  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: ABHD6 localizes to postsynaptic spines of glutamatergic neurons in adult mouse prefrontal cortex (Figure 5G-H). Localization of ABHD6 is juxtaposed (not overlapping) with presynaptic CB1-receptors which bind 2-AG, the lipid metabolized by ABHD6. Supplementary Figure 9 shows ABHD6 is mainly expressed glutamatergic neurons and to a lesser extent GABAergic interneurons and some astrocytes.\n\nPostsynaptic membrane annotation: ABHD6 is an integral membrane protein (active site faces cytoplasm).\n\n5/12/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Electron microscopy: C57BL/6 mice; adulte, cortical layers 4-5 (Fig 5)\nCell type and synapse type immunostaining: C57BL/6 mouse cortical sections (sup. Fig 9)" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9783-5183" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5676-366X" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1929" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

